# Architecture Rules

Open-core architecture. Define interfaces before implementations.

- The Go module for the open source eIM core lives at the repository root and uses module path github.com/openiotrsp/openiotrsp.
- Three extension interfaces are the contract for the enterprise build: Store, Signer, TenantResolver. Keep them stable and documented.
- Protocol logic (asn1, euiccpkg, esipa, smdp, pki) lives in exported packages so the enterprise module can import it. Do not put protocol logic under internal/.
- Depend on the Store, Signer, and TenantResolver interfaces, never on a concrete implementation, in protocol code.
- Every per-device or per-fleet table and storage method carries a tenant_id, defaulted to a single value in the open source build.
